#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.29:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Uruvelavagga "
msgstr "3. At Uruvelā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Dhammapadasutta "
msgstr "29. Basic Principles "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.29:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, dhammapadāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni porāṇāni asaṅkiṇṇāni asaṅkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four basic principles are original, long-standing, traditional, and ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them. "

msgctxt "an4.29:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.29:1.3"
msgid "Anabhijjhā, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "Contentment, good will, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.29:2.1"
msgid "Abyāpādo, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.29:3.1"
msgid "Sammāsati, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.29:4.1"
msgid "Sammāsamādhi, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.29:4.2"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri dhammapadāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni porāṇāni asaṅkiṇṇāni asaṅkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhīti. "
msgstr "These four basic principles are original, long-standing, traditional, and ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.29:5.1"
msgid "Anabhijjhālu vihareyya, "
msgstr "You should live with contentment, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.29:5.2"
msgid "abyāpannena cetasā; "
msgstr "and a heart of good will, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ekaggacittassa → ekaggacittāyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.29:5.3"
msgid "Sato ekaggacittassa, "
msgstr "mindful, with unified mind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.29:5.4"
msgid "ajjhattaṃ susamāhito”ti. "
msgstr "serene within.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.29:5.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
